      "span_text": "12,  Tauber et al demonstrate a slightly higher incidence of delayed ICH and observed clinically significant consequences in half of those cases.  It is interesting to note that their study included only patients on ASA therapy, which, in our study, proved to be an independent statistically significant risk factor for ICH when included in the therapeutic regimen, as did clopidogrel, while anticoagulant agents alone did not."
